subSubSection.paragraph:
Generally, the ventral plate of halacarids consists of an anterior epimeral, right and left posterior epimeral, and genital and anal plates or a single genitoanal plate. Genital and anal plates are fused into a genitoanal plate in many halacarid genera. Although an anal plate is generally separated from a genital plate in the initial nymphal stages, these two plates are fused into a single genitoanal plate during ontogenesis. Therefore, the basic number of ventral plates is regarded to be four in adult halacarids (
Abé 1998
).
